<br>
I was busy on another CR from trying to solo PoS trash mobs when suddenly I ran into a level 65 Beast Lord that was happily killing frogs, the ones near the GY and other trash.<br>
<br>
I took some time to watch him in action and noticed that these blue to me, and blue to him mobs were dying in about 3 or 4 minutes.  He went like that for about 30 minutes then saw me and stopped.  The basic conclusion of my conversation with him was that he used his best slow spell, used his pet and both healed his bet and meleed/dotted.<br>
<br>
He asked how much or even if I could solo in PoS and I had to admit I could not solo very well, at best I was doing 1 tree every 20 - 25 minutes.  I also had to admit that many times, maybe 1/3 of my engaments I would die.<br>
<br>
Well, my parsings of his pets damage and his damage clued me in to the fact that with Slow BL &gt; Mages when it comes to soloing, especially in PoP.<br>
<br>
Level 61+ and Epic pets alike get eaten so fast in PoP.  Why?  Its not the Pets Power but the fact we do not have slow.  We don't need Snare or Root... we need Damage Mitigation!<br>
<br>
So what does this have to do with Pets?<br>
<br>
Since giving us Slow would cause Shaman, Enchanters, and Beast Lords to go nuts on SoE there is no way were goign to get what would help us the most which is a 45% slow at 65.<br>
<br>
Instead of this I propose that the level 61 Air pet be given the ability to proc a 40% slow and that all our pets recieve increased damage mitigation capabilties (by 30%).<br>
<br>
This is simple.. and yes it limits us to soloing with 1 pet in PoP but its a slolution that benifits all.  It woudl give mages the ability to solo again like they should have had in the first place with PoP.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2706<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 2:51:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=990.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The Pet Solution?</span><hr size=1> The problem with slow is that if you measure it's power per person, you'll find that it's most useful in a solo situation.  A group of 6 shamans will be able to get something slowed really quickly, but stacking 6 slows isn't going to slow the mob down 6x more than usual.<br>
<br>
That's where working together comes in and the fact that this isn't a one-player game.  3-4 minutes per mob is a hell of a long time to take to kill something, especially if there is a possibility for adds.  If you'd group together, you could get the defensive slow power from the beastlord, and he will gain your offensive ability.  He'll also be able to buff your mana regen, and you can give him mod rods.<br>
<br>
As for your suggestion:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Instead of this I propose that the level 61 Air pet be given the ability to proc a 40% slow and that all our pets recieve increased damage mitigation capabilties (by 30%).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->As I mentioned in another thread, a pet being able to proc slow would be an extremely powerful ability.  One of the main drawbacks of slow is the aggro it draws.  You could slow a mob with almost no penalty at all.<br>
<br>
As for increasing mitigation abilities, you would have to join the crowd of melees currently complaining about the amount of damage they take in PoP.<br>
<br>
<br>
