<br>
Correct me if I am wrong, but haste is maxed at something like 100% or so.  So at best, haste doubles the DPS and thus effective power of a PC.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, slow is often 65-75%, which effectively quarters the damage output of the mob.  Not only is it therefore twice as effective as haste, but unlike haste, buys time to cast spells and fight longer.  A 75% slow has the same net effect as quadrupling the hit points of the main tank, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">and</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> quadrupling all healing and regeneration effects.  Or seen another way, as it quadruples the time the group can sustain the fight, it is also like quartering the casting time of all spells, and giving melees 300% haste, both beyond existing caps.<br>
<br>
Slow makes a mockery of healing and any supposed intra-priest class balance.<br>
<br>
The fact that slow is such a profound ability makes me hesistant to ask for any form of it.  If we need something like that, I think we should seek other forms of mitigation, like stuns.<br>
<br>
